WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.289 --> 00:00:01.029
Welcome.

1
00:00:01.250 --> 00:00:03.809
Let's talk about something incredibly important,

2
00:00:04.050 --> 00:00:05.929
trauma informed practice,

3
00:00:06.329 --> 00:00:09.890
especially when it comes to supporting young adults like Billy Buntingham,

4
00:00:10.130 --> 00:00:12.210
who navigates life with ADHD.

5
00:00:12.489 --> 00:00:13.710
Imagine Billy,

6
00:00:13.949 --> 00:00:14.640
he's bright,

7
00:00:14.890 --> 00:00:15.930
full of energy,

8
00:00:16.090 --> 00:00:18.200
and sees the world a little differently.

9
00:00:18.850 --> 00:00:19.110
Sometimes

10
00:00:19.489 --> 00:00:21.559
that difference can lead to challenges,

11
00:00:21.729 --> 00:00:26.190
and those challenges might stem from experiences he's had that have left a mark.

12
00:00:26.569 --> 00:00:28.399
Trauma isn't always obvious.

13
00:00:28.600 --> 00:00:29.670
It can be subtle.

14
00:00:29.840 --> 00:00:32.959
A quiet undercurrent affecting how someone feels,

15
00:00:33.099 --> 00:00:33.549
learns,

16
00:00:33.599 --> 00:00:34.709
and interacts.

17
00:00:35.250 --> 00:00:37.830
Trauma informed practice means approaching Billy,

18
00:00:37.959 --> 00:00:39.979
not just with his ADHD in mind,

19
00:00:40.400 --> 00:00:44.619
but with an understanding that past experiences might be shaping his present.

20
00:00:44.799 --> 00:00:46.419
It's about creating a safe,

21
00:00:46.759 --> 00:00:48.950
supportive environment where he feels seen,

22
00:00:49.200 --> 00:00:49.560
heard,

23
00:00:49.680 --> 00:00:51.900
and understood without judgment.

24
00:00:52.099 --> 00:00:56.959
It's about recognizing that his reactions might be a response to something deeper

25
00:00:57.119 --> 00:00:59.560
and responding with empathy and patience.

26
00:01:00.090 --> 00:01:03.220
This approach empowers him to build resilience and thrive,

27
00:01:03.430 --> 00:01:06.230
recognizing his strengths and unique perspective.

28
00:01:06.540 --> 00:01:08.660
Thank you for joining this conversation.

29
00:01:08.959 --> 00:01:10.349
If you found this helpful,

30
00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:12.639
consider following for more insights.